{
  "stem": "1581.4",
  "chunk_idx": 3,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 8.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And one day, we were lined up to become tattooed on our forearm, and while we were standing in line, a-- a commander came and said, you, you, you, and you, and picked out a few of us, and we were given winter coats, which was already an enormous luxury because it was freezing.",
      "word_count": 54
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And we were marched with the usual amenities, like whipping, and beatings, and shootings.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "We were marched to the trail, and again, we were put in a railroad-- into a cattle train.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "This time, we got a piece of bread on our trip, and so things were looking up.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And we were on the train two full days until we arrived at the place, at a railroad station with the name of Kaufering.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Six days.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "That's all.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, Theresienstadt was a trenchant ghetto.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "As we saw, even Birkenau was a trenchant ghetto.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Most of the people, I mean over 90%, were killed right there and then.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But the ones who were fit were destined to die in another way.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "That is, through work and starvation.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So we arrived in Kaufering, which I later learned is one of the branches, or one of the slave labor camps, attached to another famous concentration camp with the name of Dachau.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And whenever we thought we have reached a low that a human being can go through, we were bitterly disappointed because we learned there is still much, much worse to come.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "The stay in Kaufering was just one of continuous horror.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We were there to be worked to death, and there was no other purpose.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Our sleeping arrangements were the old barracks like in Birkenau.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "We had appel after appel, no decent clothes.",
      "word_count": 8
    }
  ],
